claims:
Claims 1. A medical imaging device, comprising: a rigid elongated member; a distal tip directly connected to the rigid elongated member, said distal tip comprises a front camera, wherein the front camera comprises a lens assembly and an image sensor providing a focal length of about 1.7 millimeters and a front camera magnification factor, wherein the front camera is located on a front planar surface of the distal tip and; a first side camera, wherein the first side camera comprises a lens assembly and an image sensor providing a focal length of about 3.4 millimeters and a first side magnification factor, wherein the first side camera is located on a lateral surface of the distal tip and positioned approximately 5 to 10 millimeters from the front planar surface of the distal tip, wherein the front camera magnification factor and the first side camera magnification factor are configured to simultaneously capture objects to further be displayed on an image monitor at similar sizes; a controller designed to receive the objects simultaneously captured by the first side camera and the front camera and display a continuous panoramic view formed by a field of view captured by the front camera and a field of view captured by the first side camera for objects which are located at a distance of about 15 to 150 millimeters from said front and first side cameras. 2. The medical imaging device of claim 1, further comprises a second side camera, wherein the second side camera comprises a lens assembly and an image sensor providing a focal length of about 3.4 millimeters and a second side camera magnification factor, wherein the second side camera is located on the lateral surface of the distal tip in opposite side to said first side camera. 3. The medical imaging device of claim 2, wherein the second side camera magnification factor and the front camera magnification factor are configured to simultaneously capture objects to further be displayed on the image monitor at similar sizes. 4. The medical imaging device of claim 1, wherein the first side camera magnification factor has a larger value than the magnification factor of the front camera for objects located at a distance of about 15 to 150 millimeters from said front and first side camera. 5. The medical imaging device of claim 4, wherein the first side camera magnification factor is twice larger than the magnification factor of the front camera for objects 

 located at a distance of about 15 to 150 millimeters from said front and first side camera. 6. The medical imaging device of claim 2, wherein the second side camera magnification factor has a larger value than the magnification factor of the front camera for objects located at a distance of about 15 to 150 millimeters from said front and second side camera. 7. The medical imaging device of claim 6, wherein the second side camera magnification factor is twice larger than the magnification factor of the front camera for objects located at a distance of about 15 to 150 millimeters from said front and second side camera. 8. The medical imaging device of claim 2, wherein the second side camera positioned closer to the front planar surface of the distal tip than the first side camera. 9. The medical imaging device of claim 2, wherein the second side camera has a horizontal field of view of between 80-120 degrees. 10. The medical imaging device of claim 2, wherein the second side camera is provided with a focal length which is different from the focal length of the front camera. 11. The medical imaging device of claim 2, wherein the first side camera has a horizontal field of view of between 80-120 degrees. 12. The medical imaging device of claim 1, wherein the front camera has a horizontal field of view of between 80-120 degrees. 13. The medical imaging device of claim 1, wherein the medical imaging device is connected to a system configured to display the view captured by the first side camera and the front side camera, in a unified and continuous panoramic view. 14. The medical imaging device of claim 13, wherein the system further comprises a controller configured to utilize a digital zoom for adjusting the magnification factors of the front camera and the first camera. 15. The medical imaging device of claim 14, wherein the controller is located at the rigid elongated member. 16. The medical imaging device of claim 14, wherein the controller is located within a control unit of said system. 17. A method for receiving similar sizes of objects captured by at least two cameras of a medical imaging device, comprising: capturing a field of view of a front camera, wherein the front camera is a video camera located at the front planer of the medical imaging device; 

 identifying the front region of interest, wherein the front region of interest is at least a portion of the field of view captured by the front camera; calculating the distance between the front camera and the front region of interest; capturing a field of view of a first side camera, wherein the first side camera is located at the lateral surface of said medical device; identifying objects appearing in the field of view captured by the first side camera; calculating the magnification factor of the front camera by utilizing the distance value measured between the front camera and the front region of interest; utilizing the magnification factor of the front camera for calculating a magnification factor of a first side camera, wherein calculating the magnification factor of the first side camera is performed to receive similar object sizes for objects simultaneously captured by the first side camera and the front camera; modulating the magnification factor of the first side camera, wherein the magnification factor of the first side camera is set according to a result of said calculation of the magnification factor of a first side camera. 18. The method of claim 17, wherein the first side camera is characterized with a magnification factor configured to increase and / or decrease thereof and thereby to allow viewing objects simultaneously captured by the second side camera and the front camera at similar sizes. 19. The method of claim 17, further comprises capturing a field of view of a second side camera, wherein the second side camera is located at the lateral surface of said medical device in opposite side to said first side camera. 20. The method of claiml8, wherein the second side camera is characterized with a magnification factor configured to increase and / or decrease thereof and thereby to allow viewing objects simultaneously captured by the second side camera and the front camera at similar sizes; 21. The method of claim 17, wherein the front camera is provided with a focal length which is different from the focal length of the first side camera. 22. The method of claim 17, wherein the front camera utilizes an image sensor. 23. The method of claim 17, wherein the first side camera utilizes an image sensor. 24. The method of claim 17, further comprises a process for determining the magnification factor by the focal lengths of the front camera and of the first side camera, wherein enlarging the focal length of the front camera and / or the first side camera results in increasing of the magnification factors of the front camera and / or the first side camera, accordingly. 25. The method of claim 17, further comprises a process for determining magnification factor by the digital zoom factor of the front camera and the first side camera, wherein enlarging of the digital zoom factor of the front camera and / or the first side camera results in increasing of the magnification factors of the front camera and / or the first side camera, accordingly. 26. The method of claim 17, further comprises displaying the view captured by the first side camera and / or the front side camera in a unified and continuous panoramic view by a system connected to the medical imaging device. 27. The method of claim 17, wherein the digital zoom factor of the front camera and / or the first side camera can be increased and / or decreased by a system connected to the medical imaging device.
